      "content": "I can optimize the function to use a more efficient algorithm. The current code checks every possible substring, which is not necessary. We can use a different approach that only checks for palindromes centered around each character.\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    n = len(s)\n    res = \"\"\n    for i in range(n):\n        # odd length palindrome\n        sub = s[i:i+1]\n        if sub == sub[::-1] and len(sub) > len(res):\n            res = sub\n        # even length palindrome\n        sub = s[i:i+2]\n        if sub == sub[::-1] and len(sub) > len(res):\n            res = sub\n    return res\n```\n\nHowever, this approach still has a time complexity of O(n^2). We can further optimize it by using a dynamic programming approach. This approach has a time complexity of O(n^2) as well, but it's much faster in practice.\n\n```python\ndef longest_palindrome(s):\n    n = len(s)\n    dp = [[False]*n for _ in range(n)]\n    res = \"\"\n    for i in range(n):\n        dp[i][i] = True\n        res = s",
